      "narrative": "LedgerBridge is developing API-based infrastructure for SME lending and is currently pre-revenue, with three lender pilots and signed LOIs. The model assumes no revenue for the next 36 months as per founder guidance (ARPC and usage are both zero). Even with the additional capital raise of £1.2M, the cash runway extends circa 16 additional months, but unless revenue milestones are achieved, the business will face a funding gap after month 16. Cost base increases 4% monthly to reflect team expansion and operational ramp-up, but without revenue conversion, the business never reaches breakeven in this window. Immediate focus must be on converting pilots and LOIs to paid contracts to extend runway and achieve a sustainable business model.",
